& [LMStudioWorkerFunctionalLane] is the functional local worker lane for booted SOP proposal jobs
  + [pattern_role] is codex_hosted_lm_studio_worker_runner_and_validator
  + [operational_host] is Codex, which owns prompt packet preparation, subprocess launch, output capture, validation, file writes, commits, pushes, and integration decisions
  + [worker_provider] is LM Studio through Codex CLI local-provider or OpenAI-compatible endpoint
  + [safe_launch_mode] is scratch_prompt_only because project-root launches still leak host context into task content authority
  + [project_root_mode] is diagnostic_only until host-context fence and validator prove negative_inside_rule compliance
  + [boot_packet] is SOPWorkerBootPacket with authority hierarchy, intent anchor, local law, exact-format latch, and negative-inside rule
  + [prompt_packet] is primer plus boot plus framework excerpt plus exact output schema
  + [capture_target] is a SOP output file under events, spool, or benchmark records
  + [validator] is Codex-side exact schema, field content, required term, forbidden inside term, outside preservation, and substitution fault check
  + [accepted_output] is worker proposal text that passes validator and remains proposal until Codex integrates it
  + [rejected_output] is captured worker text that fails validator and becomes evidence for retry, fence tuning, or block
  + [spool_record] is the visible worker tree record containing prompt reference, launch command, result file, validation state, and authority boundary
  + [launch_queue_candidate] is a TaskFrameLaunchQueue candidate that is ready_for_inspection before Codex decides whether to launch
  + [readiness_profile] is complete-corpus limited-diverse scratch-isolated, prompt-only, non-mutating SOP proposal readiness with six distinct Codex-validated strong task-family signals and a compiled synthesis record
  + [readiness_evidence_count] is 6 distinct strong task-family validations, 17 preserved attempts, and earlier same-family stability evidence
  + [readiness_profile_record] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\events\benchmarks\lm_studio_worker_readiness_profile_20260624_008.sop
  + [readiness_synthesis_record] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\events\benchmarks\lm_studio_worker_readiness_synthesis_20260624_016.sop
  + [first_pilot_queue] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\events\task_queues\2026-06-24_lmstudio_limited_worker_pilot_queue_001.sop
  + [first_pilot_result] is pressure_impact_thinkabout_016 accepted retry_001 as score 100 strong after task-fit latch rejected one validator-strong external-example drift
  + [functional_definition] is a local worker can complete a non-mutating booted SOP inference job in scratch_prompt_only mode, produce exact SOP output, pass validator, and return captured proposal text for Codex review
  + [manager_lane_extension] is LM Studio may act as a local manager over Codex-authored context streams by returning codex_job_proposal text only
  + [manager_context_stream] is the Codex-authored current focus, task frame, source slice, attention kernel, queue state, expected output, gates, and outside
  + [manager_proposal] is one proposed OpenAI Codex CLI job or blocked_outside note that must pass Codex review before launch
  + [manager_transport_preference] is direct LM Studio OpenAI-compatible endpoint when Codex CLI local-provider prompt overhead exceeds the effective local context
  + [local_manager_primary_correction] is routine manager attention should use direct local LM Studio and lightweight SOP context streams before involving OpenAI Codex
  + [next_readiness_gate] is draft the accepted pressure impact ThinkAbout record under Codex authority before considering any broader lane claim
  + [task_corpus] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\LMStudioWorkerTaskCorpus.sop
  + [block_condition] is provider unavailable, Codex CLI unavailable, context overflow, no-tool failure, exact-format failure, negative-inside failure, hidden-state overclaim, or repeated local-law substitution after boot and validator retry
  + [lane_outside] is repo mutation by worker, direct trust of worker output, hidden model state, credentials, broad competence, and project-root authority until fenced

  ? [use_when: LM Studio should perform a small Codex-directed SOP worker job]
    = activate [LMStudioWorkerFunctionalLane]

  = must: use scratch_prompt_only as the default launch mode for functional local worker jobs
  = must: use project_root_mode only as a diagnostic benchmark until negative_inside_rule passes
  = must: capture raw worker output before validation
  = must: enter TaskFrameLaunchQueue before launch when used by SOPTaskManager
  = must: reject output when validator finds missing fields, Markdown format, forbidden inside terms, missing required local-law terms, or substitution faults
  = must: preserve rejected output as benchmark evidence rather than silently repairing it
  = must: record functional worker runs in a spool record when task orchestration or future re-entry matters
  = must: keep accepted output as proposal text until Codex review integrates it
  = must: treat readiness_profile as limited-diverse only for scratch_prompt_only non-mutating SOP proposal jobs
  = must: keep manager_lane_extension non-mutating and proposal-only until Codex launch review accepts a proposed job
  = must: prefer direct endpoint local_manager_primary_correction for low-reasoning queue management
  = must: require manager_context_stream, SOP language primer, boot packet, capture target, and validator before manager proposal work
  = must: use the readiness synthesis before selecting a limited worker pilot queue or broadening any lane claim
  = must: treat validator-strong external-example drift as rejected until task-fit latch passes
  = should: retry with stricter boot only when failure suggests prompt ambiguity rather than model incapacity
  - never: grant file mutation or repo authority to LM Studio worker output
  - never: let LM Studio manager output directly launch OpenAI Codex jobs or claim completed Codex work
  - never: call the lane fully functional for project-root jobs while AGENTS.md leakage remains
  - never: treat repeated same-family validation score 100 as broad competence proof

(lm_studio_worker_functional_lane) :prompt_packet: /boot_packet and validator/ |lane_outside|
  + [prompt_packet] is primer plus boot plus local law plus exact schema
  + [boot_packet] is authority hierarchy and intent-context guard
  + [validator] is host-side proof that output obeyed the task boundary
  + [accepted_output] is validated proposal text only
  + [spool_record] is visible task tree and launch receipt
  |lane_outside| worker mutation, hidden state, unvalidated output, project-root leakage, and broad competence claims

/ [SOPWorkerBootPacket], [CodexOperationalHost], [LMStudioProvider] -(Launches)> [scratch_prompt_only_worker], [captured_output], [spool_record], [lane_outside]
* [captured_output], [validator], [CodexReview] -(AcceptsOrRejects)> [accepted_output], [rejected_output], [next_gate]
